label.value: Stage 0 Hypopharyngeal Squamous Cell Carcinoma AJCC v6, v7, and v8

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0.  Tis: Carcinoma in situ.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th, 7th, and 8th eds.)
A benign smooth muscle neoplasm arising from the trachea. It is characterized by the presence of spindle cells with cigar-shaped nuclei, interlacing fascicles, and a whorled pattern.
A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from the pars distalis of the anterior pituitary gland.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from the pars distalis of the anterior pituitary gland.
A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from the pars intermedia of the anterior pituitary gland.

A synthetic derivative of phenylpiperazine with broad antifungal properties and potential antineoplastic activity.  Ketoconazole inhibits sterol 14-a-dimethylase, a microsomal cytochrome P450-dependent enzyme, thereby disrupting synthesis of ergosterol, an important component of the fungal cell wall. (NCI04)
A rare malignant soft tissue neoplasm that arises from the trachea.
